-- Falling Temperatures May Spur Brazil Frost, Forecaster Says
-- B y   M a r v i n   G .   P e r e z
-- 2012-05-01T20:24:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/falling-temperatures-may-spur-brazil-frost-forecaster-says.html
Falling temperatures in south  Minas
Gerais , the top coffee-producing state in Brazil, may cause
frost overnight, according to the government’s Meteorology
Institute, known as Inmet.  “Meteorological conditions are favorable” for frost,
Inmet said in a statement posted today on its  website .  Brazil  is the world’s biggest coffee producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marvin G. Perez in New York at 
 mperez71@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
